Week 1: Fundamentals of Web Development
HTML Basics:
Understanding the structure of web pages.
Learning essential tags like <div>, <h1> to <h6>, <p>, <img>, <a>, and forms.
Creating simple static web pages.
CSS Introduction:
Styling web pages using properties like colors, fonts, padding, margins, and borders.
Exploring CSS selectors, classes, and IDs.

Week 2: Introduction to Interactivity
JavaScript Fundamentals:
Learning variables, data types, operators, and functions.
DOM manipulation for adding dynamic behavior to web pages.
Event handling (e.g., onclick, onmouseover).
Responsive Design Concepts:
Understanding media queries for device compatibility.
Implementing layouts for different screen sizes.

Week 3: Frameworks and Tools
Bootstrap CSS:
Using the grid system for layout design.
Implementing pre-designed components like buttons, modals, and navigation bars.
Tailwind CSS:
Learning utility-first styling.
Creating responsive, modern UI elements using Tailwind classes.

Week 4: Project Development
Developing UI projects using Tailwind CSS to implement the skills learned:
Designing a portfolio website.
Creating a landing page for a fictional product.
Adding interactivity using JavaScript.


